Definition:
------------
Factory design pattern is a creational design pattern that provides an interface for creating objects in a super class,
but allows subclasses to alter the type of objects that will be created.

* Provides an interface for creating objects without exposing the object creation logic to the client.

          Payment (Interface)
                |
   ------------------------------
   |            |               |
UpiPayment  CreditCardPayment  PaypalPayment

                |
           PaymentFactory
                |
              Client


Advantages of Factory Pattern
------------------------------
1. Loose Coupling
    Client does not know the concrete class.

2. Follows Open/Closed Principle
    You can add a new payment type without modifying client code.
    Example: BitcoinPayment
    Only add new class + update factory.

3. Centralized Object Creation
    All object creation happens in one place.

4. Encapsulation of Object Creation Logic
    Complex creation logic is hidden from client.

5. Promotes Code Reusability
    Common code for creating objects can be reused in factory.

How This Applies to E-Commerce Architecture
--------------------------------------------
Factory pattern can be used for:
        Module	        Factory Example
        Payment	        PaymentFactory
        Shipping	    ShippingFactory
        Notification	NotificationFactory
        Discount	    DiscountStrategyFactory